## <a id="reqs"></a>Requirements


Before you can begin the steps detailed in this document, you must have the following software installed in your servers:

* PCF Apps Manager 1.7.x or above
* PCF Ops Manager 1.7.x or above
* Cloud Foundry CLI
* Python 2.x or above
* Anypoint Platform On-Premises Edition
* The default Java buildpack that PCF provides

**Note:** Your Anypoint Platform and PCF installations must both be on the same network in order for them to be able to communicate with each other.

After following the steps in this document, you must also:
* Install the Mule Runtime BuildPack
* Run the Space Configuration Tool

**Note:** See [MuleSoft documentation]() for details on how to carry out these steps.


## <a id="limitations"></a>Limitations

Each instance of the PCF Tile is linked to one PCF cluster, and every instance of the Space Configuration Tool is linked to one PCF space. Therefore, if you wish to manage multiple PCF spaces or multiple PCF clusters, you must also perform multiple installations of the Anypoint Platform Service Brokers for PCF and the Space Configuration Tool to match these.

